# mBot2 RuVector Companion - Environment Variables
# Copy to .env and fill in your values:  cp .env.example .env
#
# Lines starting with # are comments (ignored).
# Remove the # before a line to enable it.
# Only MBOT_TELEGRAM_TOKEN is needed for basic Telegram control.
# All other keys are optional and enable extra features.

# ─── Telegram Bot (for controlling robot from your phone) ─────────────────────
#
# Get a token: open Telegram, message @BotFather, send /newbot, follow prompts.
# Paste the token here (no quotes needed):
# MBOT_TELEGRAM_TOKEN=

# ─── Text-to-Speech (gives the robot a voice) ────────────────────────────────
#
# Sign up at https://elevenlabs.io, go to Profile > API Keys, copy your key.
# Without this, the robot still works — it just won't speak.
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=

# ElevenLabs voice ID (default: 21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM = Rachel)
# Browse voices at https://elevenlabs.io/voice-library
# MBOT_VOICE_ID=21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM

# ─── Speech-to-Text (for microphone input on phone) ──────────────────────────
#
# Only needed if you want to speak to the robot via the phone UI microphone.
# Groq is faster and has a free tier. OpenAI is the fallback.
# GROQ_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# ─── LLM Brain Layer (experimental, --brain flag) ────────────────────────────
#
# Gives the robot LLM-powered reasoning. Not needed for basic voice commands.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Claude model (default: claude-sonnet-4-20250514)
# MBOT_CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-20250514

# Ollama local fallback (free, runs on your machine)
# Install Ollama: https://ollama.ai, then: ollama pull llama3.2
# MBOT_OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434
# MBOT_OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.2

# LLM tuning
# MBOT_LLM_TIMEOUT_SECS=30
# MBOT_LLM_MAX_TOKENS=512
# MBOT_LLM_TEMPERATURE=0.7

# ─── Discord Bot (alternative to Telegram) ───────────────────────────────────
# MBOT_DISCORD_TOKEN=

# ─── Voice API URL (for Telegram bridge, default: http://localhost:8088) ──────
# MBOT_VOICE_API_URL=http://localhost:8088
